 62fc2931-b921-4cee-95e4-5fc39956f6a3.dab30efd-f798-404c-a025-4f7d35242b07.description=e1cfeaf0-3767-47c5-b879-82d3acdb61f6.95c20b57-b6a6-479d-a241-754412032962.description 62fc2931-b921-4cee-95e4-5fc39956f6a3.description=<pre>
 Purpose

Restore an Oracle backup file onto a target Oracle database server.

 Description

The Database Refresh is a restore task conducted via Oracle's RMAN utility in conjunction with the use of backup file(s), archived logs and a control file from a defined source database. The RMAN files provided and target server are then subjected to a series of validation checks. If the file(s) together with the target database server passes through the prerequisite checks, the backup files will then be restored onto the target database server. Appropriate messages will be provided along the course of the workflow should any issues arises.

After the actual RMAN restore has been accomplished, the workflow performs the necessary database checks ensuring the the database is accessible, temporary tablespace has been created and that no tablespaces are in backup mode. Appropriate messages are depicted should any of the database checks fails.

 Dependencies

Target DB server must be on Oracle 11.1.0 or higher and on an Enterprise Edition.
Oracle Software and database must be provision on target database prior to workflow execution.
Target database server must be in archive log mode.
The 'Target Directory' where RMAN files are to be downloaded must be created prior to execution of the workflow. Oracle account user must have read/write access on the pre-created target directory.
For RMAN backup files\: database structure, database name, and Oracle SID has to match that of source. Should the Oracle database name and SID be different from source the DBID has to be provided prior to the refresh activity.

 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 Database ID - *Required\: DB ID of the source database.
 Instance.Name - No description
 Instance.os user - No description
 RMAN Archive Logs - *Required\: Archived log files generated from source database via RMAN. Separate multiple files with a comma.
 RMAN Control File - *Required\: Control File generated from source database.
 RMAN Data Files - *Required\: RMAN backup of datafiles from source database. Separate multiple files with a comma.
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 Server.Become User - No description
 Target Directory - *Required\: Directory where RMAN backup files are to be downloaded on target database server. Must be known to the Oracle Account.

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 Verification Result - *Optional\: File containing result of the "Verification SQL Script".
 Verification SQL Script - *Optional\: File containing sql commands used to verify the refresh completed correctly.
 Oracle Account - *Optional\: Oracle user that will own the ORACLE_HOME. Required if inventory does not exist. Left blank for Windows.
 RMAN Tags - *Optional\: Tag to search for in proposed RMAN archive file.
 Ignorable Oracle Errors - *Optional\: Comma delimited list of Oracle errors to ignore while executing the import. Example\: ORA-31684,ORA-39111

 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the RESOURCES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
</pre> 62fc2931-b921-4cee-95e4-5fc39956f6a3.ee86d580-0c61-4e50-923c-733eca7d499e.description=Purpose\:
